snippet.textDisplay: I really HATE this series. There are not 4 levels - there's only cheap, modest, and expensive. If I wanted a hot dog I wouldn't spend $50 to make 6 of them, nor would I mistakenly call a bratwurst a hot dog, nor would I buy a cheap hot dog and boil it. Give them all the same amount of money and see what they do with it. An expert in hot dogs would have made a great chili, a hot pepper relish, and stopped wasting expensive ingredients that add nothing. This series reminds me of an old sci-fi movie where the chef adds a tiny bit of feces then tells the customer they need an educated pallet to taste it correctly.
